title: CX My Heart and the Superbowl of Single Speed CX
description:
A post-season race for fun to keep things rolling a little longer. But we’re doing things a little bit differently: The Elites always get to
sleep in, so we’re going to run the race order backwards so the Cat 4 can catch a break for
once. Also, the mid-atlantic\'s only dedicated single speed category.  

If the fields for certain races are too small, we reserve the right to combine races or change race
times. You will still be in a different category, but will be racing at the same time as another race.
course: The course will be over a variety of surfaces:  pavement, grass, dirt, gravel and mulch.  There are a few natural barriers, a set of stairs and a set of traditional cyclocross barriers.
registration:
All pre-registration must be done online using bikereg.com  
pre-registration will close at 7PM on Thursday Feb 4th.

Race day registration will be available for an additional $10.  This is the first race of 2010.  Please make sure to renew your license online.  Anyone without a valid 2010 USACycling license will be required to purchase a 1 day category 4 license.  

On race day, registration will close 15 minutes before each race.  

Any racer registering for more than one race will get a $10 discount on each additional race.
notes:
If the fields for certain races are too small, we reserve the right to combine races or change race
times. You will still be in a different category, but will be racing at the same time as another race.
directions:
Driving Directions:


From Baltimore

Take 95 South to Washington DC.  At the interchange with 495, follow all signs to College Park Maryland. You will get on 495, merge briefly, then exit the beltway onto US -1 Baltimore Avenue towards College Park. Stay in the right lane. The next major intersection will be with Cherry Hill Road, at a large shopping center (last stop for coffee – there is a starbucks) and make a right onto Cherry Hill road. Take Cherry Hill Road about one mile and make a right onto Jay Rose Blvd. You will be directed to more parking from here.

From Washington DC

Option 1:

Take Rhode Island avenue out all the way to college park. Male a left on Cherry Hill Road, at a large shopping center (last stop for coffee – there is a starbucks).  Take Cherry Hill Road about one mile and make a right onto Jay Rose Blvd. You will be directed to more parking from here.  Please note that if you reach a sign for the beltway, you have missed the road and you should turn around. 

Option 2:

Take New Hampshire Avenue all the way out of DC until you get to University Bldv (193) and make a left on University. Take Universtity all the way until you reach an onramp for route 1, and take the 2nd ramp to get to US 1 / Baltimore Blvd. Take US 1 and make a left on Cherry Hill Road, at a large shopping center (last stop for coffee – there is a starbucks). Take Cherry Hill Road about one mile and make a right onto Jay Rose Blvd. You will be directed to more parking from here. Please note that if you reach a sign for the beltway, you have missed the road and you should turn around. 

From Virginia

Take 95 / 495 North to the exit for US 1, and take the exit towards Washington DC. The next major intersection will be with Cherry Hill Road, at a large shopping center (last stop for coffee – there is a starbucks) and make a right onto Cherry Hill road. Take Cherry Hill Road about one mile and make a right onto Jay Rose Blvd. You will be directed to more parking from here.

title: Michael P. Murad Memorial Road Race
description:
Michael P. Murad Memorial Road Race
Presented by
All American Bicycle Club
Saturday, May 1, 2010 in Poolesville, MD 
Held Under USA Cycling Permit
course: Race is run on a rolling 8-mile loop in Poolesville, MD.  MAP.  Centerline rule will be in effect and enforced.
registration:
Entry fee for all races is $35, which includes the BikeReg registration fee of $3.00.  No Mail in Registration – online or  race day only.  Race-day entry fee is $40 (which includes a late fee).  Register online at http://www.bikereg.com.  Online registration ends 4/26/2010.  Race-day registration opens at 7:00 a.m. and closes 15 minutes prior to each race.  Unattached rider fee of $5 (except for Men 5/Women 4).  Transfers will be allowed up to 4/16/2010.  No transfers will be made after that date.   Entry fees will not be refundable under any circumstances.
All USA Cycling rules apply.  For Info:  Matt McGoey at raceinfo@aabikes.com or online at the All American Bicycle Center website, http://www.aabikes.com.
notes:
Riders who are lapped or out of contention may be pulled at officials’ discretion.
The centerline rule will be vigorously enforced.
Each race will be followed by a wheels in/wheels out support vehicle. Race promoter is not responsible for lost or missing wheels.
The following events (listed parenthetically) are included in the following BAR competitions: Novice Women BAR (Women 4); Senior Women BAR (Women 1/2/3/4); Men Masters 35+ 3/4 BAR (Men Masters 35+ 3/4); Novice Men BAR (Men 4); Senior Men BAR (Men Pro/1/2); and Senior 3 Men BAR (Men 3).
Women will race together but will be scored separately, and separate prizes will be awarded, for each of the Senior Women BAR and the Novice Women BAR, respectively.
directions:
From DC Beltway- I-270 North to Exit 10 (Clopper Road).  Take a right at light at the end of the exit ramp.  Take a left on Quince Orchard Rd (Rt 124).  Follow approximately 3 miles to Rt 28W/Darnestown Road.  Take a right onto 28W and follow approximately 6 miles.  Veer left onto Rt 107/Whites Ferry Road towards Poolesville.  Follow approximately 4 miles and take a left on Wooton Ave.  Proceed on Wooton approximately .2 miles and take a left onto Hughes Road.  Follow signs to race parking. 
For Mapquest/Googlemaps:  Search intersection of Hughes Road and Sugarland Road, Poolesville, MD 20837
